Paragraph we have chosen:
But a sober look at our world shows that the degree of human intervention, often in the service of business interests and consumerism, is actually making our earth less rich and beautiful, ever more limited and grey, even as technological advances and consumer goods continue to abound limitlessly. We seem to think that we can substitute an irreplaceable and irretrievable beauty with something which we have created ourselves.

Prepare a short, informal presentation for sharing with the class

Slide 1
Title: Just because we can intervene by collecting data, should we?
Exerpt: "The degree of human intervention often in the service of business interests and consumerism is making our earth...more limited"
Commentary:
Data analysis in consumerism and other business interests can restrict our abilities to see the world as something other than ones and zeros
This begs the question, at what point do we stop trying to organize things into categories and just accept intricacy without trying to simplify it

Slide 2
Title: Is artificial intelligence undermining the beauty of the human mind?
Exerpt: "We seem to think we can substitute an irreplaceable and irretrievable beauty with something which we have created ourselves"
Commentary:
We discussd in class computers like Watson diagnosing better than doctors can
Is the human brain too intricate and irreplaceable for artificial intelligence, are we undermining the complexity of humans by trying to create machines that think like them?
